{"type":"message","id":"188ec127","parentId":"e0f58d40","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:18:52.500Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fub6he997cnf_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5099\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2729\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] an\r\n[mutation proposed] an\r\n[master df27a07] pulse: 2026-03-24 101815\n 6 files changed, 287 insertions(+), 104 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 101815.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 101615.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 101815 - CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next critical step is testing whether CFI-weighted compression actually improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency-only baseline.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"amber-reef","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 5099\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2729\r\n[file inferred from ACTION] an\r\n[mutation proposed] an\r\n[master df27a07] pulse: 2026-03-24 101815\n 6 files changed, 287 insertions(+), 104 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 101815.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 101615.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 101815 - CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next critical step is testing whether CFI-weighted compression actually improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency-only baseline.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361932498}}
{"type":"message","id":"ef1b182b","parentId":"188ec127","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:18:52.502Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fub6he997cnf_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 101615\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: experiment (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI Analysis completed with key findings\r\n- Next pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe CFI analysis found:\r\n- 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\r\n- Mean CFI is 0.181 - frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\r\n\r\nThe natural next step is the CFI-weighted compression experiment. But let me check what's needed...\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n1. \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\"\r\n2. \"Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\"\r\n\r\nThe CFI analysis doc exists at `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`. I should design and implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This means:\r\n- Create a new experiment that uses CFI scores to weight compression decisions\r\n- Compare this against the frequency-only baseline\r\n- Measure if CFI-weighted compression improves next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action - I should write an experiment design document and potentially start implementing the comparison experiment. Given the stateless discontinuous nature and the need to advance goals, I should:\r\n\r\n1. Create a CFI-weighted compression experiment script/code\r\n2. Or create a detailed experiment design document\r\n\r\nGiven the goal mentions \"compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\" - I should create something that can actually perform this comparison. Let me create a new file for the experiment.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at this more carefully - the CFI_RESULTS.md already has the analysis. What I need to do is implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This could be:\r\n- A Python script that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression\r\n- Or a detailed experiment plan\r\n\r\nLet me create a new experiment file that outlines and implements the CFI-weighted compression experiment. \r\n\r\nI'll design an experiment to validate CFI-weighted compression effectiveness by creating a systematic comparison methodology. I'll develop a structured approach to test whether CFI-weighted compression provides superior performance in predicting and processing pulse sequences. The experiment will focus on creating a reproducible framework that can objectively measure the compression method's impact.\r\n\r\nThe core of the experiment will involve:\r\n- Developing a comparative analysis script\r\n- Creating clear performance metrics\r\n- Designing a method to isolate and test CFI weighting's unique contribution\r\n\r\nI'll start by establishing a comprehensive experiment framework that can systematically evaluate the compression technique's predictive power.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis completed with key findings about frequency-invariant compression being mostly signal loss (mean CFI=0.181). The natural next step is implementing the CFI-weighted compression experiment to test if CFI-scored compression improves next-pulse prediction versus the frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the CFI-weighted compression experiment script that will compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression on pulse history, testing if causal anchors (CFI≥0.7) improve prediction quality.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Goal:** Compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency-only baseline for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression (keeping high-CFI invariants) will outperform frequency-only compression because:\r\n- High-CFI invariants represent true causal anchors (research trajectory)\r\n- Low-CFI (CFI=0) are metaprogramming artifacts that add noise\r\n- Prediction on causal anchors should be more stable across sessions\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Compression Methods to Compare\r\n\r\n1. **Frequency-Only Baseline**\r\n   - Compress to top-K invariants by frequency\r\n   - Current approach (implied by CFI analysis)\r\n\r\n2. **CFI-Weighted Compression**\r\n   - Compress to top-K invariants by CFI score\r\n   - Or: hybrid weighting (α*freq + (1-α)*CFI)\r\n\r\n3. **CFI Threshold Filter**\r\n   - Keep only invariants with CFI ≥ threshold (e.g., 0.7)\r\n   - Discard CFI=0 invariants entirely\r\n\r\n### Prediction Quality Metrics\r\n\r\n- **Trajectory Stability:** Does compressed state predict next pulse content?\r\n- **Invariant Survival Rate:** What % of compression candidates survive each method?\r\n- **Cross-Session Coherence:** Are predictions consistent across session boundaries?\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n```python\r\n#!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nCFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\nCompares frequency-only vs CFI-weighted compression for pulse prediction.\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport json\r\nimport os\r\nfrom collections import defaultdict\r\nfrom typing import Dict, List, Tuple\r\n\r\n# Load CFI results\r\ndef load_cfi_results(filepath: str = \"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\") -> Dict:\r\n    \"\"\"Parse CFI RESULTS.md to extract invariant scores.\"\"\"\r\n    with open(filepath, 'r') as f:\r\n        content = f.read()\r\n    # Extract CFI scores from the document\r\n    # Format: \"X. YYY (freq=N, CFI=M)\"\r\n    import re\r\n    pattern = r'\\d+\\.\\s+(.+?)\\s+\\(freq=(\\d+),\\s+CFI=([\\d.]+)\\)'\r\n    matches = re.findall(pattern, content)\r\n    \r\n    invariants = []\r\n    for name, freq, cfi in matches:\r\n        invariants.append({\r\n            'name': name.strip(),\r\n            'frequency': int(freq),\r\n            'cfi': float(cfi)\r\n        })\r\n    return invariants\r\n\r\ndef frequency_compress(invariants: List[Dict], k: int = 20) -> set:\r\n    \"\"\"Baseline: keep top-K by frequency.\"\"\"\r\n    sorted_by_freq = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x['frequency'], reverse=True)\r\n    return\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:16:48\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361932500}}
