{"type":"message","id":"fd1d0292","parentId":"002f441e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:01.222Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_g7eobb8s27xu_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 5099\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='' new_len=2729\n[file inferred from ACTION] an\n[mutation proposed] an\n[master df27a07] pulse: 2026-03-24 101815\n 6 files changed, 287 insertions(+), 104 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 101815.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 101615.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 101815 - CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next critical step is testing whether CFI-weighted compression actually improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency-only baseline."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"amber-reef","total":10,"totalLines":10,"totalChars":733,"truncated":false,"exitCode":0,"name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361941220}}
{"type":"message","id":"f0baecfe","parentId":"fd1d0292","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:08.849Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me also check the actual created files to give a complete summary.\n\nSummary:\n1. Pulse script ran successfully\n2. Previous pulse (101615) had created a mutation that was rejected (moved to rejected folder)\n3. New pulse (101815) created:\n   - `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md` - session log\n   - `mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 101815.mutation` - the proposed mutation\n4. The mutation was a new file creation (an empty placeholder that got rejected) - the LLM tried to create `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md`\n\n\n5. The git diff shows 6 files changed with 287 insertions and 104 deletions, indicating this pulse involved more substantive changes than the previous one.","thinkingSignature":"97db777b88d87e7307df79711ec9a7ef8c1b589052952f5e9c82c756f956adf0"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_derdtsrw9947_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-24 101815.mutation"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2116,"output":232,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14485,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774361941223}}
{"type":"message","id":"30a4ef40","parentId":"f0baecfe","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:08.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_derdtsrw9947_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"an\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\n# Compare: Frequency-only vs CFI-weighted compression for next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [int]$TopN = 50,        # Number of top invariants to consider\n    [float]$CFIThreshold = 0.7  # Minimum CFI to be considered \"causal\"\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSScriptRoot -Parent) -Parent\n\n# Load CFI results\n$CFIFile = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\"\nif (-not (Test-Path $CFIFile)) {\n    Write-Error \"CFI_RESULTS.md not found. Run CFI analysis first.\"\n    return\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\nWrite-Host \"TopN: $TopN, CFI Threshold: $CFIThreshold\"\nWrite-Host \"\"\n\n# Parse CFI data (simplified - extract invariant-CFI pairs)\n# Expected format: Each invariant has line like \"CFI: 0.XXX\"\n$InvariantData = @()\n\n# Load all frequency-invariants from experiments directory\n$ExperimentsDir = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"experiments\"\n$InvariantFiles = Get-ChildItem $ExperimentsDir -Filter \"*.md\" -Recurse | \n    Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"frequency_invariant\" } |\n    Select-Object -First 20\n\nWrite-Host \"Found $($InvariantFiles.Count) invariant files\"\n\nforeach ($File in $InvariantFiles) {\n    $Content = Get-Content $File.FullName -Raw\n    \n    # Extract frequency and CFI if available\n    if ($Content -match \"frequency:\\s*(\\d+)\" -and $Content -match \"CFI:\\s*([\\d.]+)\") {\n        $InvariantData += [PSCustomObject]@{\n            File = $File.Name\n            Frequency = [int]$Matches[1]\n            CFI = [float]$Matches[2]\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"Parsed $($InvariantData.Count) invariant entries\"\n\n# Strategy 1: Frequency-only compression (current baseline)\n$FreqTop = $InvariantData | Sort-Object Frequency -Descending | Select-Object -First $TopN\n$FreqCompressionRatio = $FreqTop.Count / $InvariantData.Count\n$FreqAvgFreq = ($FreqTop | Measure-Object Frequency -Average).Average\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy 1: Frequency-Only Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\nWrite-Host \"Selected $($FreqTop.Count) invariants\"\nWrite-Host \"Compression ratio: $([math]::Round($FreqCompressionRatio * 100, 1))%\"\nWrite-Host \"Average frequency: $([math]::Round($FreqAvgFreq, 1))\"\n\n# Strategy 2: CFI-weighted compression (proposed)\n$CFIInvariantData = $InvariantData | Where-Object CFI -ge $CFIThreshold\n$CFITop = $CFIInvariantData | Sort-Object Frequency -Descending | Select-Object -First $TopN\n$CFIPrevalence = ($CFIInvariantData.Count / $InvariantData.Count) * 100\n\nWrite-Host \"\"\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy 2: CFI-Weighted Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Green\nWrite-Host \"Causal invariants (CFI>=$CFIThreshold): $($CFIInvariantData.Count) ($([math]::Round($CFIPrevalence, 1\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361948855}}
