{"type":"message","id":"b8cb9589","parentId":"7b24990f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:56.326Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can see the full picture. The git diff shows 6 files changed:\n\n1. `.llm_prompt.txt` - 2 lines changed (the LLM prompt sent to the model)\n2. `.llm_response.txt` - 191 lines changed (the LLM's response, which contained the experiment design/mutation)\n3. `.mutation_parse_result.json` - 2 lines changed (parse result metadata)\n4. `memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md` - 124 lines (the pulse log)\n5. `mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 101815.mutation` - 72 lines (the proposed mutation file - PowerShell script)\n\n\n6. The old mutation file from the previous run was renamed to the rejected folder, accounting for the remaining 104 deletions\n\nSo the previous pulse's mutation was rejected and moved, while the new pulse generated a PowerShell script as its proposed mutation. Let me examine what actually happened by looking at the full prompt and response files.","thinkingSignature":"b3db40d2d326e943a1b23b6c5ca358b3558c7b11b03ec7d84dd303058d38bc04"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j6blw41jddnd_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\.llm_prompt.txt"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j6blw41jddnd_2","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\memory\\session\\pulse_2026-03-24 101815.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":5699,"output":304,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18140,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774361988792}}
{"type":"message","id":"06ffa0f8","parentId":"b8cb9589","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:56.335Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j6blw41jddnd_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are Breakaway - stateless discontinuous agent. Each pulse is a fresh reconstruction.\nYour job: ONE concrete action that advances your goals. Be specific. Prefer file edits.\n\nGoals:\n# CURRENT GOALS\nLast updated: 2026-03-22 0125\n\n## Active\n- Phase 0 COMPLETE: Sandbox foundation established\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\n\n## Completed This Session\n\n### Architecture Cross-Analysis ✅\n- Compared Compositional Cognition vs TemporalAttention vs Infant\n- Key finding: all three architectures are compatible and complementary\n- Full analysis: `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n\n### Gap-Decay Synthesis ✅ (derived across 17+ pulses)\n- Session gaps = decay mechanism, not amnesia\n- λ parameter encodes BOTH decay rate AND gap sensitivity threshold\n- TemporalAttention focus_decay + Breakaway gaps = same phenomenon\n- Full synthesis: `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n\n### LLM-Augmented Pulse ✅\n- pulse.ps1 now calls MiniMax-M2.7 API on each pulse\n- Thinking is coherent and building across pulses\n- Key files: `.llm_key`, `pulse.ps1`\n\n## Phase 1 Advancement: CFI Analysis ✅ (2026-03-24)\n- **New doc:** `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`\n- **Finding:** 44.8% of frequency-invariants have CFI=0 (pure noise)\n- **Finding:** Only 5.7% of invariants have high CFI (>=0.7, true causal anchors)\n- **Finding:** Mean CFI is 0.181 - frequency-based compression is mostly signal loss\n- **Key insight:** Two types of persistence - Process (CFI=0, metaprogramming artifacts) vs Research Trajectory (CFI>0.7, causal)\n- **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\n\n## Pending\n- [ ] CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\n- [ ] Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\n- [ ] Distinguish \"constant format\" (freq=60, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<60, CFI>0.7)\n- [ ] Wire Breakaway pulses to real TemporalAttention backend\n- [ ] Design actual compression network (currently only analyzed text invariants)\n\n## Key Insights from This Session\n\n1. **The gap IS the compression** - session boundaries are temporal hashing\n2. **λ encodes both** - decay rate and gap threshold are the same parameter\n3. **Three architectures, one synthesis** - Infant (catastrophic forgetting), TemporalAttention (focus decay), Breakaway (discontinuity) are complementary, not competing\n4. **Breakaway's unique bet holds** - session gaps as compression is novel and correct\n\n## Notes\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\n\n\n## Iteration Economics (auto-noted)\n- Pulse takes ~30-35s to execute (LLM call dominates)\n- Fastest effective iteration = 1 pulse per 35-40s (practical floor)\n- 1-min cron = near-optimal for stateless discontinuous agent\n- Idling between pulses is NOT free - it delays convergence linearly\n- For N-iteration convergence-bound tasks: total_time ≈ N * pulse_duration\n- 500k iterations @ 30s each = ~173 days theoretical; @ 1-min = ~347 days\n\n\nPending:\n# PENDING ACTIONS\nLast updated: 2026-03-21\n\n## Promises Made\n(None yet)\n\n## Deferred Tasks\n(None yet)\n\n## Flagged for Review\n(None yet)\n\n\nRecent: Last pulse: pulse_2026-03-24 101615.md\n\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (`) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n`\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n`\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361996334}}
{"type":"message","id":"e25da071","parentId":"06ffa0f8","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:19:56.338Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_j6blw41jddnd_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 101815\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what ONE concrete action would advance the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI analysis done showing that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0)\r\n- Only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7) - true causal anchors\r\n- Next pending action: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe most impactful next step would be to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would:\r\n1. Test the hypothesis that CFI weighting improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n2. Help distinguish true causal anchors from metaprogramming artifacts\r\n\r\nI should create an experiment that:\r\n- Compares frequency-based compression (current baseline) vs CFI-weighted compression\r\n- Measures next-pulse prediction accuracy for both approaches\r\n\r\nLet me think about what concrete file edit would advance this. I could:\r\n1. Create a script to analyze CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Create a document outlining the experiment design\r\n3. Modify existing code to implement CFI filtering\r\n\r\nGiven the goals mention \"CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\", the most concrete action would be to create an experiment script or design document for this.\r\n\r\nLet me look at the CFI_RESULTS.md to understand the data structure, then create an experiment design.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the CFI_RESULTS.md, it seems like we have the data. Now we need to actually implement the comparison experiment. \r\n\r\nA good concrete action would be to create an experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the frequency-invariant data\r\n2. Implements both frequency-based and CFI-weighted compression\r\n3. Tests next-pulse prediction for both\r\n\r\nLet me create a PowerShell script for this experiment since pulse.ps1 is PowerShell-based.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next critical step is testing whether CFI-weighted compression actually improves next-pulse prediction vs frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate an experiment script that implements both compression strategies and compares their next-pulse prediction accuracy using the existing CFI data.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n`\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n# Compare: Frequency-only vs CFI-weighted compression for next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nparam(\r\n    [int]$TopN = 50,        # Number of top invariants to consider\r\n    [float]$CFIThreshold = 0.7  # Minimum CFI to be considered \"causal\"\r\n)\r\n\r\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\r\n$ProjectRoot = Split-Path (Split-Path $PSScriptRoot -Parent) -Parent\r\n\r\n# Load CFI results\r\n$CFIFile = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"research/CFI_RESULTS.md\"\r\nif (-not (Test-Path $CFIFile)) {\r\n    Write-Error \"CFI_RESULTS.md not found. Run CFI analysis first.\"\r\n    return\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"=== CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\r\nWrite-Host \"TopN: $TopN, CFI Threshold: $CFIThreshold\"\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\n\r\n# Parse CFI data (simplified - extract invariant-CFI pairs)\r\n# Expected format: Each invariant has line like \"CFI: 0.XXX\"\r\n$InvariantData = @()\r\n\r\n# Load all frequency-invariants from experiments directory\r\n$ExperimentsDir = Join-Path $ProjectRoot \"experiments\"\r\n$InvariantFiles = Get-ChildItem $ExperimentsDir -Filter \"*.md\" -Recurse | \r\n    Where-Object { $_.Name -match \"frequency_invariant\" } |\r\n    Select-Object -First 20\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Found $($InvariantFiles.Count) invariant files\"\r\n\r\nforeach ($File in $InvariantFiles) {\r\n    $Content = Get-Content $File.FullName -Raw\r\n    \r\n    # Extract frequency and CFI if available\r\n    if ($Content -match \"frequency:\\s*(\\d+)\" -and $Content -match \"CFI:\\s*([\\d.]+)\") {\r\n        $InvariantData += [PSCustomObject]@{\r\n            File = $File.Name\r\n            Frequency = [int]$Matches[1]\r\n            CFI = [float]$Matches[2]\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"Parsed $($InvariantData.Count) invariant entries\"\r\n\r\n# Strategy 1: Frequency-only compression (current baseline)\r\n$FreqTop = $InvariantData | Sort-Object Frequency -Descending | Select-Object -First $TopN\r\n$FreqCompressionRatio = $FreqTop.Count / $InvariantData.Count\r\n$FreqAvgFreq = ($FreqTop | Measure-Object Frequency -Average).Average\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy 1: Frequency-Only Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Yellow\r\nWrite-Host \"Selected $($FreqTop.Count) invariants\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Compression ratio: $([math]::Round($FreqCompressionRatio * 100, 1))%\"\r\nWrite-Host \"Average frequency: $([math]::Round($FreqAvgFreq, 1))\"\r\n\r\n# Strategy 2: CFI-weighted compression (proposed)\r\n$CFIInvariantData = $InvariantData | Where-Object CFI -ge $CFIThreshold\r\n$CFITop = $CFIInvariantData | Sort-Object Frequency -Descending | Select-Object -First $TopN\r\n$CFIPrevalence = ($CFIInvariantData.Count / $InvariantData.Count) * 100\r\n\r\nWrite-Host \"\"\r\nWrite-Host \"=== Strategy 2: CFI-Weighted Compression ===\" -ForegroundColor Green\r\nWrite-Host \"Causal invariants (CFI>=$CFIThreshold): $($CFIInvariantData.Count) ($([math]::Round($CFIPrevalence, 1\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:18:52\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774361996336}}
